üìò PART B: ASSIGNMENT ANSWERS (VERY IMPORTANT FOR CCEE)
‚úÖ 1) Difference between UTP & STP
Feature	UTP	STP
Full form	Unshielded Twisted Pair	Shielded Twisted Pair
Shielding	No shielding	Shielded
Interference	More EMI	Less EMI
Cost	Cheaper	Costly
Usage	LAN, Ethernet	Industrial networks
‚úÖ 2) Categories of Cables
CAT3 ‚Äì Telephone networks
CAT5 ‚Äì 100 Mbps
CAT5e ‚Äì 1 Gbps (Enhanced)
CAT6 ‚Äì 10 Gbps (short distance)
CAT6a ‚Äì High-speed LAN
CAT7 ‚Äì Shielded, high bandwidth
‚úÖ 3) Meaning of ‚Äúe‚Äù in CAT5e
‚û° ‚Äúe‚Äù stands for Enhanced

Better crosstalk control
Higher speed than CAT5
Supports Gigabit Ethernet
